Due to recent floods in Venezuela, President Hugo Chávez announces the erection in his garden of a Bedouin tent given as a gift by Muammar al-Gaddafi from which he is to live and govern to make room for more homeless families in his presidential palace at Miraflores. 25 families made homeless by the disaster had already sought shelter there and Chávez has been personally supervising the provision of relief in the country. (BBC)Wreckage of a Tara Air de Havilland Canada DHC-6 Twin Otter that crashed on Wednesday with twenty people aboard is found in Nepal. (BBC), (CNN)